Chilean Stocks: Cap, Empresas Copec and Lan Airlines Decline

-- B y   J a m e s   A t t w o o d
-- 
2011-10-04T15:44:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/chilean-stocks-cap-empresas-copec-and-lan-airlines-decline.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:44 a.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 3.5 percent to 3,630.93. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index retreated 5.3 percent to 1,915.20.  Cap SA (CAP)   dropped 4.2 percent to 14,599 pesos, the
lowest price since December 2009.  Chile ’s largest iron miner and
steel producer slumped along with industrial metal prices amid
concern that demand may weaken as a worsening European
sovereign-debt crisis saps economic growth.  Empresas Copec SA (COPEC CC) fell for a third day, slumping
3.6 percent to 5,800 pesos. Chile’s biggest pulp exporter
declined along with weekly pulp prices released today. The BHKP
pulp index fell 3.5 percent, the most since December 2008,
according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  Lan Airlines SA (LAN)   slid 2.7 percent to 10,240 pesos,
poised for the lowest closing price since July last year. Lan
will push ahead with its acquisition of  Brazil ’s Tam SA as it
appeals to Chile’s  Supreme Court  to overturn some restrictions
antitrust authorities imposed on the $2.7 billion transaction,
the two airlines wrote in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Attwood in Santiago at 
 Jattwood3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
